    <abstract>
      <t>Consider an end-to-end Multipoint LDP (mLDP) network, where it is desirable to deploy BIER in a segment of this network. It might be desirable to deploy BIER with minimal disruption to the mLDP network or a redesign of the network. This document describes a procedure needed for mLDP tunnels to be signaled over and stitched through a BIER core, allowing LDP routers to run traditional mLDP services through a BIER core.</t>
    </abstract>
